<item>
            <title>[LU-16353] Config variable enable_crypto must not contain special characters</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16353</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;enable_crypto&quot; shell variable&#160; used in autoconf/lustre-core.m4 and config/lustre-build.m4 is sometimes used unquoted, so it is unsafe for it to contain special characters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It can be set to &quot;embedded llcrypt&quot; which contains a space.&#160; This causes errors when running ./configure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This appears to be the only enable_foo variable that has this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
